{"name": "opentelemetry-instrumentation-together", "metadata": {"name": "opentelemetry-instrumentation-together", "version": "0.33.12", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/traceloop/openllmetry/tree/main/packages/opentelemetry-instrumentation-together", "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["opentelemetry-api", "opentelemetry-instrumentation", "opentelemetry-semantic-conventions", "opentelemetry-semantic-conventions-ai"], "summary": "OpenTelemetry Together AI instrumentation", "upload_time": 1731529662}, "documentation": ["# OpenTelemetry Together AI Instrumentation\n\n<a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/opentelemetry-instrumentation-together/\">\n    <img src=\"https://badge.fury.io/py/opentelemetry-instrumentation-together.svg\">\n</a>\n\nThis library allows tracing calls to any of Together AI's endpoints sent with the official [Together AI Library](https://github.com/togethercomputer/together-python).\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install opentelemetry-instrumentation-together\n```\n\n## Example usage\n\n```python\nfrom opentelemetry.instrumentation.together import TogetherAiInstrumentor\n\nTogetherAiInstrumentor().instrument()\n```\n\n## Privacy\n\n**By default, this instrumentation logs prompts, completions, and embeddings to span attributes**. This gives you a clear visibility into how your LLM application is working, and can make it easy to debug and evaluate the quality of the outputs.\n\nHowever, you may want to disable this logging for privacy reasons, as they may contain highly sensitive data from your users. You may also simply want to reduce the size of your traces.\n\nTo disable logging, set the `TRACELOOP_TRACE_CONTENT` environment variable to `false`.\n\n```bash\nTRACELOOP_TRACE_CONTENT=false\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together.utils.dont_throw", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["A decorator that wraps the passed in function and logs exceptions instead of throwing them.\n\n@param func: The function to wrap\n@return: The wrapper function"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together.version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together.version.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together.config", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together.config.Config", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together.config.Config.exception_logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together", "documentation": ["OpenTelemetry Together AI instrumentation"], "functions": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together.should_send_prompts", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together._set_span_attribute", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "span", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.together._set_input_attributes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "span", "type": 